 I could modify the placeholder to a public class with a no-op, but it's still not active. Should I leave it as is? Also, I need to think about naming. The file should be called MethodUtilsTest.java, without any dollar signs. Okay, I need to create that file!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_G4m2iW5PG7NVp20GNeH2Dq2Z|fc_055da6fec84f077e0169f7778ebdd8819484e807033e5991f6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/MethodUtilsTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.apache.commons.beanutils.MethodUtils;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class MethodUtilsTest {\n\n    @BeforeEach\n    public void disableMethodCache() {\n        MethodUtils.setCacheMethods(false);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void invokeMethodFindsCompatibleInstanceMethodAndInvokesIt() throws Exception {\n        InvocationTarget target = new InvocationTarget();\n\n        Object result = MethodUtils.invokeMethod(target, \"repeat\", new Object[]{Integer.valueOf(3)},\n                new Class[]{Integer.class});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"valuevaluevalue\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void invokeExactMethodFindsExactInstanceMethodAndInvokesIt() throws Exception {\n        InvocationTarget target = new InvocationTarget();\n\n        Object result = MethodUtils.invokeExactMethod(target, \"echo\", new Object[]{\"beanutils\"},\n                new Class[]{String.class});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"echo:beanutils\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void invokeStaticMethodFindsCompatibleStaticMethodAndInvokesIt() throws Exception {\n        Object result = MethodUtils.invokeStaticMethod(InvocationTarget.class, \"sum\",\n                new Object[]{Integer.valueOf(4), Integer.valueOf(5)}, new Class[]{Integer.class, Integer.class});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(Integer.valueOf(9));\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void invokeExactStaticMethodFindsExactStaticMethodAndInvokesIt() throws Exception {\n        Object result = MethodUtils.invokeExactStaticMethod(InvocationTarget.class, \"staticEcho\", new Object[]{\"core\"},\n                new Class[]{String.class});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"static:CORE\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void getAccessibleMethodFindsPublicMethodThroughInterfaceNest() {\n        Method method = MethodUtils.getAccessibleMethod(HiddenInterfaceImplementation.class, \"fromParentInterface\",\n                new Class[]{String.class});\n\n        assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(method.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(ParentInterface.class);\n        assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"fromParentInterface\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void getAccessibleMethodFindsPublicMethodThroughSuperclass() {\n        Method method = MethodUtils.getAccessibleMethod(HiddenSubclass.class, \"superclassOnly\",\n                new Class[]{String.class});\n\n        assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(method.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(PublicBase.class);\n        assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"superclassOnly\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void getMatchingAccessibleMethodUsesDirectLookupWhenSignatureMatches() {\n        Method method = MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod(InvocationTarget.class, \"echo\",\n                new Class[]{String.class});\n\n        assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(method.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(InvocationTarget.class);\n        assertThat(method.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(String.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void getMatchingAccessibleMethodScansPublicMethodsWhenOnlyCompatibleSignatureExists() {\n        Method method = MethodUtils.getMatchingAccessibleMethod(InvocationTarget.class, \"repeat\",\n                new Class[]{Integer.class});\n\n        assertThat(method).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(method.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(InvocationTarget.class);\n        assertThat(method.getParameterTypes()).containsExactly(int.class);\n    }\n\n    public interface ParentInterface {\n        String fromParentInterface(String value);\n    }\n\n    public interface ChildInterface extends ParentInterface {\n    }\n\n    private static class HiddenInterfaceImplementation implements ChildInterface {\n        @Override\n        public String fromParentInterface(String value) {\n            return \"interface:\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class PublicBase {\n        public String superclassOnly(String value) {\n            return \"superclass:\" + value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class HiddenSubclass extends PublicBase {\n    }\n\n    public static class InvocationTarget {\n        public String echo(String value) {\n            return \"echo:\" + value;\n        }\n\n        public String repeat(int count) {\n            StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder();\n            for (int i = 0; i < count; i++) {\n                builder.append(\"value\");\n            }\n            return builder.toString();\n        }\n\n        public static String staticEcho(String value) {\n            return \"static:\" + value.toUpperCase();\n        }\n\n        public static int sum(int left, int right) {\n            return left + right;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 516, "output": 2755, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28359, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777825654510, "responseId": "resp_055da6fec84f077e0169f77776fef48194803627f6cbc57e4a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_G4m2iW5PG7NVp20GNeH2Dq2Z|fc_055da6fec84f077e0169f7778ebdd8819484e807033e5991f6", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 5013 bytes to tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/MethodUtilsTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777825684091}]}
